    <title>
      <narrative xml:lang="en">Technical Assistance for Budget and Financial Accountability</narrative>
    </title>
    <description type="1">
      <narrative xml:lang="en">Assist the Technical Assistance Unit of the South African National Treasury in developing approaches to funding decisions and performance monitoring for information and communication technology projects. This goal of the project is to: create the organizational capacity within the National Treasury to oversee and manage ICT funding decisions; restructure the organizational responsibilities, roles and responsibilities of the Government Chief Information Officer; redefine the Department Chief Information Officers role, consolidating Department ICT functions under this position and establishing the Officers cross-departmental responsibility for ICT integration and synergy; establish within the Department of Management and Evaluation the responsibility for monitoring ICT projects and indicators and for problem-solving through a problem response team; redesign the State Information Technology Agency by relocating the ICT purchasing function to another entity, reassigning dedicated department application staff to those departments and verifying service offering benefits through a rate benchmark analysis. .</narrative>
    </description>
